==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin '''serratus''', ''saw shaped'' from '''serra''', ''saw''.

===Adjective===
'''serrated'''
# [[saw]]-like.
#:''That knife has a '''serrated''' blade.''
# Having a row of [[sharp] or [[tooth]]-like [[projection]]s.
#:''Maple leaves have '''serrated''' edges.''

===Usage note===
:''serated'' is a common misspelling of serrated.

